{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Y1vAZrQcgRtCnjbK6jkAGg","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\" standalone=\"no\"?>\n     2→<server description=\"defaultServer\">\n     3→\t<featureManager>\n     4→\t\t<!--\n     5→    \t<feature>jakartaee-9.1</feature>\n     6→    \t<feature>microprofile-5.0</feature>\n     7→\t\t-->\n     8→    \t<feature>jakartaee-10.0</feature>\n     9→    \t<feature>microprofile-6.0</feature>\n    10→\t\t<!--\n    11→            <feature>restfulWS-3.1</feature>\n    12→            <feature>jsonbContainer-3.0</feature>\n    13→            <feature>jsonpContainer-2.1</feature>\n    14→            <feature>jsonb-3.0</feature>\n    15→            <feature>jsonp-2.1</feature>\n    16→            <feature>cdi-4.0</feature>\n    17→            <feature>expressionLanguage-5.0</feature>\n    18→            <feature>concurrent-3.0</feature>\n    19→            <feature>jdbc-4.2</feature>\n    20→            <feature>web-6.0</feature>\n    21→            <feature>faces-4.0</feature>\n    22→\t\t-->\n    23→\t</featureManager>\n    24→\n    25→\t<include location=\"userRegistry.xml\"/>\n    26→\n    27→\t<httpSession idLength=\"56\" cookieHttpOnly=\"false\" cookieName=\"JSESSIONID\" invalidationTimeout=\"8h\"/>\n    28→\n    29→\t<ltpa expiration=\"8h\" keysFileName=\"${server.config.dir}/resources/security/ltpa.keys\"\n    30→\t\t  keysPassword=\"{xor}KixsLS8+ZZ2=\"/>\n    31→\n    32→\t<applicationMonitor updateTrigger=\"mbean\" />\n    33→\n    34→\t<httpEndpoint id=\"defaultHttpEndpoint\" host=\"*\" httpPort=\"8080\" httpsPort=\"8443\">\n    35→\t\t<accessLogging filepath=\"${server.output.dir}/logs/http_defaultEndpoint_access.log\"\n    36→\t\t\t\t\t   logFormat='%h %i %u %t \"%r\" %s %b %D %{R}W' />\n    37→\t</httpEndpoint>\n    38→\n    39→\t<logging consoleLogLevel=\"INFO\" />\n    40→\t<logging traceSpecification=\"*=info:RRA=all:com.ibm.ws.postgresql.logwriter=all\" />\n    41→\t<logging jsonAccessLogFields=\"logFormat\"/>\n    42→\n    43→\t<remoteFileAccess>\n    44→\t\t<writeDir>${server.config.dir}/dropins</writeDir>\n    45→\t</remoteFileAccess>\n    46→\n    47→\t<serverCommands startServerTimeout=\"240\" stopServerTimeout=\"240\"/>\n    48→\n    49→\t<variable name=\"io_openliberty_guides_system_inMaintenance\" value=\"false\"/>\n    50→\n    51→\t<dataSource id=\"DefaultDataSource\"\n    52→\t            jdbcDriverRef=\"postgresqlDriver\"\n    53→\t            jndiName=\"jdbc/datasources/PostgreSQLDS\"\n    54→\t            transactional=\"true\"\n    55→\t            type=\"javax.sql.ConnectionPoolDataSource\">\n    56→\n    57→\t\t<properties databaseName=\"petclinic_jakartaee_liberty\"\n    58→\t\t            password=\"petclinic_jakartaeepwd\"\n    59→\t\t            portNumber=\"5432\"\n    60→\t\t            serverName=\"localhost\"\n    61→\t\t            user=\"petclinic_jakartaee\"/>\n    62→\t</dataSource>\n    63→\n    64→\t<jdbcDriver id=\"postgresqlDriver\"\n    65→\t            javax.sql.ConnectionPoolDataSource=\"org.postgresql.ds.PGConnectionPoolDataSource\"\n    66→\t            javax.sql.XADataSource=\"org.postgresql.xa.PGXADataSource\"\n    67→\t            libraryRef=\"postgresqlLibrary\"/>\n    68→\n    69→\t<library id=\"postgresqlLibrary\">\n    70→\t\t<file name=\"${server.config.dir}/lib/global/postgresql.jar\"/>\n    71→\t</library>\n    72→\n    73→\t<applicationManager autoExpand=\"true\"/>\n    74→\n    75→\t<trustAssociation id=\"petclinicSso\" disableLtpaCookie=\"false\" />\n    76→\n    77→\t<ssl id=\"defaultSSLConfig\" trustDefaultCerts=\"true\" verifyHostname=\"false\"/>\n    78→\n    79→\t<keyStore id=\"defaultKeyStore\" password=\"mpKeystore\"/>\n    80→\n    81→\t<logging maxFfdcAge=\"2d\"/>\n    82→\n    83→\t<application location=\"petclinic.war\" type=\"war\"\n    84→\t\t\t\t id=\"petclinic.war\"\n    85→\t\t\t\t name=\"petclinic.war\" context-root=\"/petclinic\">\n    86→\t\t<application-bnd>\n    87→\t\t\t<security-role name=\"AllAuthenticated\">\n    88→\t\t\t\t<special-subject type=\"ALL_AUTHENTICATED_USERS\" />\n    89→\t\t\t</security-role>\n    90→\t\t\t<security-role name=\"admin\">\n    91→\t\t\t\t<group name=\"Manager\" />\n    92→\t\t\t\t<group name=\"TeamLead\" />\n    93→\t\t\t</security-role>\n    94→\t\t\t<security-role name=\"user\">\n    95→\t\t\t\t<group name=\"Employee\" />\n    96→\t\t\t</security-role>\n    97→\t\t</application-bnd>\n    98→\t</application>\n    99→</server>\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011mw7aSnQNtUqZWpkC1xoCw","session_id":"c5bd7990-ebbe-4b4c-8bc8-ce64a20596ca","uuid":"e3819e1a-20b6-4af4-a14b-ee62c1655cfb"}
