{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011FoYzMZNJ6STQDWHqPvFiA","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.vet;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.ejb.EJB;\n     4→import jakarta.ejb.Stateless;\n     5→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n     6→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n     7→import jakarta.ws.rs.PathParam;\n     8→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    10→import lombok.extern.java.Log;\n    11→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.vet.api.VetDto;\n    12→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.vet.api.VetListDto;\n    13→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.vet.db.VetService;\n    14→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.vet.api.VetEndpointUtil;\n    15→\n    16→\n    17→import java.io.Serializable;\n    18→import java.util.List;\n    19→\n    20→/**\n    21→ * Created with IntelliJ IDEA.\n    22→ * User: tw\n    23→ * Date: 05.01.14\n    24→ * Time: 09:27\n    25→ * To change this template use File | Settings | File Templates.\n    26→ */\n    27→@Log\n    28→@Path(\"/vet\")\n    29→@Stateless\n    30→public class VetEndpoint implements Serializable {\n    31→\n    32→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 607664665910620584L;\n    33→\n    34→    @EJB\n    35→    private VetService vetService;\n    36→\n    37→    @EJB\n    38→    private VetEndpointUtil vetEndpointUtil;\n    39→\n    40→    @GET\n    41→    @Path(\"/list\")\n    42→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    43→    public List<VetDto> getList() {\n    44→        log.info(\"getList\");\n    45→        return this.vetEndpointUtil.dtoListFactory(vetService.getAll()).getVetList();\n    46→    }\n    47→\n    48→    @GET\n    49→    @Path(\"/{id}\")\n    50→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    51→    public VetDto getEntity(@PathParam(\"id\") Long id) {\n    52→        log.info(\"getEntity\");\n    53→        return this.vetEndpointUtil.dtoFactory(vetService.findById(id));\n    54→    }\n    55→\n    56→    @GET\n    57→    @Path(\"/list+json\")\n    58→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    59→    public List<VetDto> getListAsJson() {\n    60→        log.info(\"getList\");\n    61→        return this.vetEndpointUtil.dtoListFactory(vetService.getAll()).getVetList();\n    62→    }\n    63→\n    64→    @GET\n    65→    @Path(\"/{id}+json\")\n    66→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    67→    public VetDto getEntityAsJson(@PathParam(\"id\") Long id) {\n    68→        log.info(\"getEntity\");\n    69→        return this.vetEndpointUtil.dtoFactory(vetService.findById(id));\n    70→    }\n    71→\n    72→    @GET\n    73→    @Path(\"/list+xml\")\n    74→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_XML)\n    75→    public VetListDto getListAsXml() {\n    76→        log.info(\"getListAsXml\");\n    77→        return this.vetEndpointUtil.dtoListFactory(vetService.getAll());\n    78→    }\n    79→\n    80→    @GET\n    81→    @Path(\"/{id}+xml\")\n    82→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_XML)\n    83→    public VetDto getEntityAsXml(@PathParam(\"id\") Long id) {\n    84→        log.info(\"getEntityAsXml\");\n    85→        return this.vetEndpointUtil.dtoFactory(vetService.findById(id));\n    86→    }\n    87→\n    88→}\n    89→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BQdcv8pxXY253KskEtmzeY","session_id":"c5bd7990-ebbe-4b4c-8bc8-ce64a20596ca","uuid":"a15d0c3a-fd4a-45b4-9190-6e236375e222"}
