{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DFWMBuyFacYFrtfdFgXYHA","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.visit.api;\n     2→\n     3→\n     4→import jakarta.ejb.Stateless;\n     5→import jakarta.json.bind.Jsonb;\n     6→import jakarta.json.bind.JsonbBuilder;\n     7→import jakarta.json.bind.JsonbException;\n     8→import jakarta.xml.bind.JAXBContext;\n     9→import jakarta.xml.bind.JAXBException;\n    10→import jakarta.xml.bind.Marshaller;\n    11→import lombok.extern.java.Log;\n    12→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.visit.Visit;\n    13→\n    14→import java.io.Serializable;\n    15→import java.io.StringWriter;\n    16→import java.util.ArrayList;\n    17→import java.util.List;\n    18→\n    19→@Log\n    20→@Stateless\n    21→public class VisitEndpointUtil implements Serializable {\n    22→\n    23→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 7444366391126982311L;\n    24→\n    25→    public VisitDto dtoFactory(Visit e) {\n    26→        VisitDto dto = new VisitDto();\n    27→        dto.setId(e.getId());\n    28→        dto.setUuid(e.getUuid());\n    29→        dto.setDate(e.getDate());\n    30→        dto.setDescription(e.getDescription());\n    31→        return dto;\n    32→    }\n    33→\n    34→    public VisitListDto dtoListFactory(List<Visit> eList) {\n    35→        List<VisitDto> dtoList = new ArrayList<>();\n    36→        for (Visit e : eList) {\n    37→            VisitDto dto = this.dtoFactory(e);\n    38→            dtoList.add(dto);\n    39→        }\n    40→        return new VisitListDto(dtoList);\n    41→    }\n    42→\n    43→    public String dtoJsonFactory(VisitDto dto) throws JsonbException {\n    44→        Jsonb jsonb = JsonbBuilder.create();\n    45→        return jsonb.toJson(dto);\n    46→    }\n    47→\n    48→    public String dtoListJsonFactory(VisitListDto listDto) throws JsonbException {\n    49→        Jsonb jsonb = JsonbBuilder.create();\n    50→        return jsonb.toJson(listDto);\n    51→    }\n    52→\n    53→    public String dtoXmlFactory(VisitDto dto) throws JAXBException {\n    54→        JAXBContext jc = JAXBContext.newInstance(VisitDto.class);\n    55→        Marshaller m = jc.createMarshaller();\n    56→        StringWriter stringWriter = new StringWriter();\n    57→        m.marshal(dto, stringWriter);\n    58→        return stringWriter.toString();\n    59→    }\n    60→\n    61→    public String dtoListXmlFactory(VisitListDto listDto) throws JAXBException {\n    62→        JAXBContext jc = JAXBContext.newInstance(VisitListDto.class);\n    63→        Marshaller m = jc.createMarshaller();\n    64→        StringWriter stringWriter = new StringWriter();\n    65→        m.marshal(listDto, stringWriter);\n    66→        return stringWriter.toString();\n    67→    }\n    68→}\n    69→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BQdcv8pxXY253KskEtmzeY","session_id":"c5bd7990-ebbe-4b4c-8bc8-ce64a20596ca","uuid":"18b3820e-c072-40af-a69c-9e3dfac666e0"}
